commit.message: add travis

fix DER encoding of odd, integral reals

The bytesNeeded calculation in putInt64be erroneously says 0 bytes are
needed to encode 0, rather than 1. Then (expLen - 1) underflows and
corrupts the Real header.

Rather than fixing putInt64be, let's just use the existing putInteger
which is already correct :)
